message.content: This question requires basic knowledge about the body's response to a lack of food. Starvation mode refers to the body's adaptive response to prolonged periods of insufficient caloric intake. When the body is not receiving enough sustenance (food and nutrients), it will start to conserve energy and slow down metabolic processes in order to survive. Options (A), (B), and (C) are not related to the body's physiological response to a lack of food.
